===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|accolade|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|oc}} {{term|acolada|lang=oc}}, from {{etyl|it}} {{term|accolata|lang=it}}, from {{term|accolare|lang=it}} to [[embrace]], from {{etyl|la}} {{term|ad-|lang=la}} + {{term|collum||neck|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An expression of [[approval]]; [[praise]].
# A special [[acknowledgment]]; an [[award]].
# {{historical}} A [[salutation]] marking the [[conferring]] of [[knighthood]], consisting of an [[embrace]] or a [[kiss]], and a slight blow on the shoulders with the flat of a sword.
# {{music}} A [[brace]] used to join two or more [[staves]].
# {{US|_|military}} Written [[presidential|Presidential]] [[certificate]] recognizing service by personnel who died or were wounded [[in action]] between 1917 and 1918, or who died in service between 1941 and 1947, or died of wounds received in [[Korea]] between June 27, 1950 and July 27, 1954. Service of [[civilian]]s who died overseas or as a result of injury or disease contracted while serving in a civilian capacity with the United States Armed Forces during the dates and/or in areas prescribed is in like manner recognized.

